Tool Used: Power BI
📁 Dataset: Superstore_Sales.csv
Columns: Order Date, Region, Category, Sales, Profit

🔧 Steps Taken
Imported Superstore_Sales.csv into Power BI

Created a new column for "Month-Year" using:
Month-Year = FORMAT([Order Date], "MMM-YYYY")

Built 3 visuals:

📈 Line Chart → Sales by Month-Year

📊 Bar Chart → Sales by Region

🍩 Donut Chart → Sales by Category

Added Slicer for Region

Used color formatting to highlight highest sales categories/regions

📸 Dashboard Screenshot or PDF
(Add this manually in GitHub repo:)
File: Sales_Dashboard_Screenshot.pdf (or .png)

📝 3–4 Key Insights (Insights.txt)
markdown
1. The West region consistently had the highest monthly sales across the year.
2. The Technology category showed the strongest performance in overall sales.
3. Sales peaked in November, likely due to seasonal promotions (Black Friday).
4. The Central region had the lowest total sales but relatively higher profit margins.
❓ Interview Q&A
Q: What does a dashboard provide in data analysis?

✅ Answer:
A dashboard provides an interactive, visual summary of data to help business users monitor performance, identify trends, and make data-driven decisions quickly.

